Always link webkit2gtk-4.1 to libslic3r_gui on Linux.

WebView.cpp references webkit_web_view_run_javascript_finish, but
Snapmaker's src/slic3r/CMakeLists.txt only adds the webkit2gtk link
inside the FLATPAK branch. On non-Flatpak Linux builds (i.e. nixpkgs
and distro-native builds) the final executable link then fails with
"DSO missing from command line".

This patch unconditionally links webkit2gtk-4.1 on Linux, matching
the upstream OrcaSlicer fix at
https://github.com/nixos/nixpkgs/blob/master/pkgs/by-name/or/orca-slicer/patches/0001-not-for-upstream-CMakeLists-Link-against-webkit2gtk-.patch
but adapted to Snapmaker's file layout (the link lives in
src/slic3r/CMakeLists.txt rather than src/CMakeLists.txt in their fork).

--- a/src/slic3r/CMakeLists.txt
+++ b/src/slic3r/CMakeLists.txt
@@ -731,6 +731,10 @@ if (UNIX AND NOT APPLE)
     target_include_directories(libslic3r_gui SYSTEM PRIVATE ${GTK${SLIC3R_GTK}_INCLUDE_DIRS} ${LIBSECRET_INCLUDE_DIRS})
     target_link_libraries(libslic3r_gui ${GTK${SLIC3R_GTK}_LIBRARIES} fontconfig ${LIBSECRET_LIBRARIES})

+    # WebView.cpp references webkit symbols directly; wxGTK does not
+    # transitively pull webkit2gtk in, so link it explicitly here.
+    pkg_check_modules(webkit2gtk REQUIRED webkit2gtk-4.1)
+    target_link_libraries(libslic3r_gui ${webkit2gtk_LIBRARIES})

     # We add GStreamer for bambu:/// support.
     pkg_check_modules(GSTREAMER REQUIRED gstreamer-1.0)
